-- ============================================================
-- Stellaris Surveillance Gaming Drills Platform
-- Craps + Caribbean Stud Poker — Question Pool Expansion
--
-- Adds, per game: 30 payout questions (odds stated in the
-- question text) + 30 shared procedure questions = 120 total.
--
-- Run ONCE in the Supabase SQL Editor AFTER seed_craps_csp.sql.
-- (Applied to production 2026-07-21 — do not re-run.)
--
-- SOURCE MANUALS (public/resources/*.pdf)
--   • Craps dealer procedures            (Updated 06-10-2020)
--   • Caribbean Stud Poker procedures     (Updated 06-09-2020)
--
-- FORMAT
--   payout questions state the odds in the text, e.g.
--   "Player bought the 4 (pays 2:1). The shooter rolls a 4.
--    How much does the dealer pay?" — the drill shows a random
--   chip stack; validation: bet × ratio (±2¢). correct_answer
--   holds the ratio as a decimal string ('2' = 2:1, '1.5' = 3:2,
--   '1.8' = 9:5, '1.4' = 7:5).
--
--   procedure questions are SHARED (game_id = NULL,
--   is_procedure = TRUE) so they surface in any session and in
--   the Procedures practice tab, like roulette_procedure:
--     category = 'craps_procedure'
--     category = 'caribbean_stud_procedure'
--
-- Difficulty is balanced 10 easy / 10 medium / 10 hard per
-- 30-question block.
-- ============================================================


